Is there any way to get good quality PDF documentation for the Kraken? Their online documentation does not have a PDF download. Making matters worse, is spread out over many web pages and each page does not print well.

I like to download PDF documentation for each device so I can annotate with notes. WCP is making this difficult.

At first glance, it looks like WCP is on the Gitbook Plus plan but the Pro plan is required for pdf export, which costs $1060 more a year at best.

And scraping wise, Gitbook’s html is obtuse and requires js to fully load the page.

Oh it looks like REV pays for Gitbook Pro. So Gitbook PDF exporter is sometimes buggy and slow and the pdf for the spark max is 189 pages anyway. I assume WCP’s docs would be a similar length.

How many hundreds of pages do you want to annotate by hand?

rsp.pdf (82.5 MB)
